conditionId.description: OEM-specific: Primary key for this condition consists of unique identifier of env. condition and DTC

diagnostic trouble codes or short DTCs are used inside ECUs to monitor failures. They were introduced for measuring vehicle emissions. Major DTCs for emissions are standardized by ISO standard ISO 15031-6:2015 - so called OBD2 standard. Over time DTCs were also introduced in other ECUs also besides engine and emission control. Many DTCs are vehicle manufacturer specific.

faultPath.description: OEM-specific: Fault path for this DTC. Allows further analysis

faultPathDescription.description: OEM-specific description of DTC fault path

freezeFrame.description: freeze frame from ecu. The freeze frame records many parameters of the DTC and surrounding parameters like outside temperature when the DTC was set. It is a very long HEX string with many OEM-specific and ECU-specific content in

fullDescription.description: description of DTC and failure byte. Both description strings are concatenated using a "-" as separator

fullName.description: Combined string of DTC name  plus the so called DTC sub type or DTC failure byte. DTC name starts with B|C|P|U + 4 hex chars + separator "-" + DTC failure byte: 2 hex chars. As this only applies for standardized DTCs there is no enforcement.

isMilOn.description: describes whether this DTC set the MIL (malfunction indicator light)  in the dashboard

occurenceCounterTotal.description: Counter how often this DTC was set in total

occurenceMileage.description: mileage in km when the DTC occurred the first time

occurenceTimeStamp.description: date and time when the DTC occured the first time/was recorded the first time in the ECU

state.description: OEM-specific state of DTC: 0;1 (permanent/temporary/intermediate), could also be a string with permanent, temporary, intermediate, ....

type.description: Indicator whether this DTC was stored as Error or Info

envConditionList.description: A list of environment conditions: E.g. outside temperature measured by the vehicle, a specific value measured by on ECU, ....

catenaXPartId.description: The fully anonymous and unique Catena-X ID of this part. This id is unique inside Catena-X data space.

calibrationVersion.description: Calibration version that was put on this ecu. A calibration file works like a parameter file for the ecu software.

oemPartName.description: Part name as defined by the original equipment manufacturer (OEM). Typically the OEM is installing the part in the car.

oemPartNumber.description: Part number of the original equipment manufacturer (OEM). Typically the OEM is installing the part in the car. A part number is NOT unique: All parts of the same kind share the same part number.

readOutDate.description: Date when this ECU information was read out from the diagnostic session

swPartNumber.description: SW part number of this ecu

swVersion.description: current version of the software on this ecu

variantCoding.description: Variant coding that was put on this ecu. Variant coding tells the ecus software how to behave.

recordStatus.description:
The record operation enumeration can be used to realize delta update concept.
Delta update concept means:
- You transfer an initial load of data
- After the first week only the delta to the initial load is transferred


The record status describes whether this record is:
- new=>This record is transferred the first time
- update=> Some properties of this record have changed compared to a previous transfer
- delete=> This record was transferred in the initial load or in a previous delta update, but is not used any more and therefore it should be deleted on data consumer side
- same=> This record was transferred in the initial load or in a previous delta update
